iHeartMedia, Inc. Key Developments

iHeartMedia, Inc. Announces Resignation of Irving L.  Azoff from the Board of Directors
May 5 17
Irving L.  Azoff resigned from the Board of Directors of iHeartMedia, Inc. effective May 3, 2017.


iHeartMedia, Inc. Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Capital Expenditure Guidance for 2017
May 4 17
iHeartMedia, Inc. reported consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the period, the company has posted revenue of $1,329,322,000 against $1,361,798,000 a year ago. Operating income was $114,057,000 against $420,714,000 a year ago. Loss before income tax was $356,896,000 against $49,381,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company was $388,215,000 against $88,496,000 a year ago. Capital expenditures for the three months ended March 31, 2017 were $51.0 million compared to $56.8 million in the three months ended March 31, 2016.

The company estimates capital expenditures for 2017 to be between $300 million and $325 million.


