iHeartMedia, Inc (formerly Clear Channel Communications)  is a media conglomerate that operates in radio and television broadcasting, domestic outdoor billboard advertising, and international outdoor advertising. The company also owns minor media operations, such as music concert promotion. The company offers its… MoreiHeartMedia, Inc (formerly Clear Channel Communications)  is a media conglomerate that operates in radio and television broadcasting, domestic outdoor billboard advertising, and international outdoor advertising. The company also owns minor media operations, such as music concert promotion. The company offers its services through AM/FM stations, HD radio stations, satellite radio, iHeartRadio mobile application on iPads and smart phones, and via navigation systems, as well as the Internet at iHeartRadio.com and radio stations’ Websites.

The company is owned by Bain Capital and Thomas H. Lee Partners.
iHeartMedia, Inc (formerly Clear Channel Communications) is a media conglomerate that operates in radio and television broadcasting, domestic outdoor billboard advertising, and international outdoor advertising. The company also owns minor media operations, such as music concert promotion. The company offers its… MoreiHeartMedia, Inc (formerly Clear Channel Communications) is a media conglomerate that operates in radio and television broadcasting, domestic outdoor billboard advertising, and international outdoor advertising. The company also owns minor media operations, such as music concert promotion. The company offers its services through AM/FM stations, HD radio stations, satellite radio, iHeartRadio mobile application on iPads and smart phones, and via navigation systems, as well as the Internet at iHeartRadio.com and radio stations’ Websites.

iHeartMedia is owned by Bain Capital and Thomas H. Lee Partners.

iHeartMedia's IT department is primarily responsible for managing the technical support requirements for the company's media operations. The department is primarily located in San Antonio, TX, but a number of IT staff are based across the US, including facilities in Phoenix, Omaha, and Denver.

The CTO leads the company's technical and IT requirements for its radio, broadcast and billboard operations. This group has oversight of the radio system operations, including the Web-based and wireless broadcast systems.

The systems group comprised of several smaller units who manage the company's internal systems for different departments, including the financial systems and support systems. A separate group administrates the quality of recorded data and application quality assurance.

The infrastructure group handles the network infrastructure and storage systems requirements. A team of system engineers oversees the data center hosting management, and operations of its networks and telecommunication systems.

The company has virtualized roughly 80 percent of its Dell application servers using VMware. Additionally, a large percentage of the company's operating systems are Microsoft-based.





